"use strict";(self.webpackChunkwebsite_docu=self.webpackChunkwebsite_docu||[]).push([[8130],{7735:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"til-pizza-box-servers","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/til-pizza-box-servers","editUrl":"https://github.com/c-shubh/website/tree/main/blog/2024-09-01-til/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-09-01-til/index.md","title":"TIL Pizza box servers","description":"TIL that those flat servers used in data centers are called pizza box servers. I came across this term while reading Computer Networking: A Top-Down Approach 8th Edition.","date":"2024-09-01T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"TIL","permalink":"/blog/tags/til","description":"Today I Learnt"}],"readingTime":0.145,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Shubh A Chudasama","url":"/","title":"Your neighborhood geek","socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/c-shubh/","github":"https://github.com/c-shubh"},"imageURL":"/img/profile-pic.png","key":"shubh","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"til-pizza-box-servers","title":"TIL Pizza box servers","tags":["TIL"],"authors":["shubh"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Obfuscate email","permalink":"/blog/obfuscate-email"}},"content":"![](pizza-box-servers.jpg)\\n\\nTIL that those flat servers used in data centers are called pizza box servers. I came across this term while reading [Computer Networking: A Top-Down Approach 8th Edition](https://gaia.cs.umass.edu/kurose_ross/index.php)."},{"id":"obfuscate-email","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/obfuscate-email","editUrl":"https://github.com/c-shubh/website/tree/main/blog/2024-08-20-obfuscate-email.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-08-20-obfuscate-email.md","title":"Obfuscate email","description":"I was building contact page for this site where I\'ve put up my email. How do I deal with bots harvesting plaintext emails from websites and sending spam?","date":"2024-08-20T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.48,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Shubh A Chudasama","url":"/","title":"Your neighborhood geek","socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/c-shubh/","github":"https://github.com/c-shubh"},"imageURL":"/img/profile-pic.png","key":"shubh","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"obfuscate-email","title":"Obfuscate email","authors":["shubh"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"TIL Pizza box servers","permalink":"/blog/til-pizza-box-servers"},"nextItem":{"title":"TIL Brave bookmarks JSON file","permalink":"/blog/til-brave-bookmarks-json-file"}},"content":"I was building [contact page](/contact) for this site where I\'ve put up my email. How do I deal with bots harvesting plaintext emails from websites and sending spam?\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nInitially I thought of using [rot13](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ROT13), but rot13 of _gmail.com_ is _tznvy.pbz_. A quick google search for _tznvy.pbz_ showed a lot of hits which might mean that it\'s a widely known and used trick to obfuscate emails and, the bots are probably aware of it too. So I went with the classic [Caesar cipher](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caesar_cipher). The only downside is that it won\'t work with JS disabled."},{"id":"til-brave-bookmarks-json-file","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/til-brave-bookmarks-json-file","editUrl":"https://github.com/c-shubh/website/tree/main/blog/2024-08-18-til.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-08-18-til.md","title":"TIL Brave bookmarks JSON file","description":"TIL that browsers store all the bookmarks in a single JSON file.","date":"2024-08-18T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"TIL","permalink":"/blog/tags/til","description":"Today I Learnt"}],"readingTime":0.255,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Shubh A Chudasama","url":"/","title":"Your neighborhood geek","socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/c-shubh/","github":"https://github.com/c-shubh"},"imageURL":"/img/profile-pic.png","key":"shubh","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"til-brave-bookmarks-json-file","title":"TIL Brave bookmarks JSON file","tags":["TIL"],"authors":["shubh"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Obfuscate email","permalink":"/blog/obfuscate-email"},"nextItem":{"title":"TIL ArrayDeque hashCode and equals","permalink":"/blog/til-arraydeque-hashcode-and-equals"}},"content":"TIL that browsers store all the bookmarks in a single JSON file.  \\nBrave stores it at this path: `%LOCALAPPDATA%\\\\BraveSoftware\\\\Brave-Browser\\\\User Data\\\\Default\\\\Bookmarks`\\n\\nThis is particularly useful if you want to programmatically manipulate or work with your bookmarks.\\n\\nSee Stack Overflow: [Parser for Exported Bookmarks HTML file of Google Chrome and Mozilla in Java](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15017163/parser-for-exported-bookmarks-html-file-of-google-chrome-and-mozilla-in-java/15106289#15106289)"},{"id":"til-arraydeque-hashcode-and-equals","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/til-arraydeque-hashcode-and-equals","editUrl":"https://github.com/c-shubh/website/tree/main/blog/2024-08-16-til.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-08-16-til.md","title":"TIL ArrayDeque hashCode and equals","description":"TIL that LinkedList overrides equals and hashCode, but ArrayDeque doesn\'t!","date":"2024-08-16T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":false,"label":"TIL","permalink":"/blog/tags/til","description":"Today I Learnt"}],"readingTime":0.225,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Shubh A Chudasama","url":"/","title":"Your neighborhood geek","socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/c-shubh/","github":"https://github.com/c-shubh"},"imageURL":"/img/profile-pic.png","key":"shubh","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"til-arraydeque-hashcode-and-equals","title":"TIL ArrayDeque hashCode and equals","tags":["TIL"],"authors":["shubh"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"TIL Brave bookmarks JSON file","permalink":"/blog/til-brave-bookmarks-json-file"},"nextItem":{"title":"Hello World!","permalink":"/blog/hello-world"}},"content":"TIL that `LinkedList` overrides equals and hashCode, but ArrayDeque doesn\'t!\\n\\nThis means that regardless of the contents of `ArrayDeque`, it gives the same `hashCode` value.  \\nThis bit me when using `Deque<T> dq = new ArrayDeque<>();`\\n\\nSee Stack Overflow: [Why doesn\'t ArrayDeque override equals() and hashCode()?](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/18203855/why-doesnt-arraydeque-override-equals-and-hashcode/18203894#18203894)"},{"id":"hello-world","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/hello-world","editUrl":"https://github.com/c-shubh/website/tree/main/blog/2024-08-05-hello-world.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-08-05-hello-world.md","title":"Hello World!","description":"Hello World!","date":"2024-08-05T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.53,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Shubh A Chudasama","url":"/","title":"Your neighborhood geek","socials":{"linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/c-shubh/","github":"https://github.com/c-shubh"},"imageURL":"/img/profile-pic.png","key":"shubh","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"hello-world","title":"Hello World!","authors":["shubh"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"TIL ArrayDeque hashCode and equals","permalink":"/blog/til-arraydeque-hashcode-and-equals"}},"content":"Hello World!\\n\\nI built my previous site using [Next.js](https://nextjs.org/) and [MUI](https://mui.com/). The other day I set up a [hugo](https://gohugo.io/) site for a friend. I have been planning to write and publish content on my website for a long time now, but never got around to do it. To reduce friction I decided to move to a platform where I don\'t have to worry about implementing all the basic blog functionality from scratch. After some research, I decided on [Docusaurus](https://docusaurus.io/). Spent an evening setting it up and achieving feature parity with my previous site, making sure to not break any URLs. Lo and behold, my new site."}]}}')}}]);